                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origDate notAfter="1250" notBefore="1151">12th century, second half, or 13th century, first half</origDate>. The layout and style of decoration in combination with the manuscript's early provenance would suggest <origPlace>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100111">France</placeName>
                                </origPlace> as the place of origin.</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>According to a note in a 15th-century hand on <locus from="222v" to="222v" scheme="folios"/>, the manuscript was given to the community at <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100270">Plessis-lèz-Tours</placeName> by <quote>Iohannes Garelli</quote>, almoner of <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102628">Louis XI</persName>. An identical note is found in <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100170">Paris, Bibliothèque Nationale</orgName>, Latin 6833, p. 161.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>Acquisition date unknown, but the manuscript has belonged to the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">National Library</orgName> since at least the 17th century; it is listed in Jaches's catalogue of 1695 (U 118:10) as no. 192 and in his catalogue of 1698 (U 122) as no. <quote>26</quote>. It is listed as no. <quote>26</quote> in the catalogue of 1734 (U 125e), and as <quote>e. 30. 3. 13</quote> in Hammarsköld's catalogue of the 19th century (U 133). The signum partially visible on the paper label at the bottom of the <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/> has not been identified.</p>
                        </acquisition>
                    </history>
