                                <incipit>CUPIENTES aliquid de penuria ac tenuitate</incipit>
                                <explicit>per media ad pedes usque uia duce peruenit</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p> As part of the planned text is included the marginal reference system for the patristic authorites associated with Lombard's commentary and developed in the schools of northern France in the 12th century (see <bibl>
                                            <title type="uniform" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107337">Rouse</title>
                                            <citedRange from="207" to="207" unit="page"/>
                                        </bibl>).</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="18A" to="18A" scheme="folios"/>: bound into the manuscript, a leaf the width of one column (stub between <locus from="22" to="22" scheme="folios"/>and <locus from="23" to="23" scheme="folios"/>), ruled and containing a total of 44 lines of text (recto and verso) in the main hand, keyed to <locus from="19rb" to="19rb" scheme="folios"/>, where the lines have been omitted.</p>
                                </note>
