                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="4r" to="221v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Marginal annotations in light brown ink by a medieval hand giving references to biblical passages and the occasional exegetical comment (e.g. <locus from="205r" to="205r" scheme="folios"/>).</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="3r" to="220r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Marginal annotations in black ink by a medieval hand indicating the number of the distinctio.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="222r" to="222r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Top of page in brown ink by a medieval hand: a list of "opinions in the Sentences which are no longer held" (<quote>opiniones magistri in sentenciis que modo non tenentur</quote>).</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="222v" to="222v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Top of page, in brown ink by a medieval hand: <quote>de iudiciis cum deputati non est credendum id est sue natio nationis</quote>. Below, in brown ink by a contemporary hand: <quote>Istud librum sententiarum legauit magister Iohannes garelli ebroicensis diocesis elemosinarius serenissimi principis Regis ludouici quondam scolarius et cappellanus collegii de plesseyo magistro et scolaribus dicti collegii de plesseyo ad usum ipsorum scolarium pro incathenando in eorum libraria et non ad alios usus applicandum</quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="223v" to="223v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Top of page, in black ink by a medieval hand: <quote>Magister Sententiarum</quote>. Below, in the same ink: <quote>88</quote>. Top and bottom of page: various pen trials. Bottom left in brown ink by a contemporary hand: <quote>Reatus idem est quod peccatum pro deformitate et culpa ut dicit magister 2 distinctione 32 capitulo 2 articulo <unclear quantity="10" unit="chars" reason="illegible"/> dicit magister hoc est enim non habere peccatum non esse remissum peccatum quibus temporibus non sunt nuptie celebrande 4 distinctione 32 capitulo ultimo </quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                            </additions>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text in brown ink; chapter rubrics in red.</p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <locus from="64r" to="64r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="111v" to="111v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="155v" to="155v" scheme="folios"/>: illuminated foliate book initials over 8-14 lines, the majority inhabited, in romanesque style in blue, red, green and brown with highlights in white and some outlining in black.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="3v" to="221v" scheme="folios"/>: plain section and chapter initials over 2-5 lines alternating in red, blue, and green with contrasting flourishing in red, blue or green, occasionally with reserved interior shapes (e.g. <locus from="215v" to="215v" scheme="folios"/>).</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1v" to="3r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="62r" to="64r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="110v" to="111v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="154r" to="155v" scheme="folios"/>: capitals in red or alternating between red and blue.</p>
